summary: Lol jk, Cyrus
question: Lol jk, Cyrus
answer:
Ok cool I adore Cyrus-

Favorite thing about them:

I love how Cyrus is just so supportive of everyone- he’s so helpful and loyal to his friends it’s so sweet. Whenever one of them has a problem he’s on his way to help :’) He’s just such an amazing and relatable character, I wish he could have his own spin-off show.

Least favorite thing about them:

I don’t personally like that he thinks when “people who haven’t done bad things to you directly” means that someone should forgive someone else who’s hurt their friend. like when Cyrus told Buffy that he should be friends with Amber since she “hadn’t actually done anything to her” while she had previously hurt Andi. (just a thought)

Favorite line: (heres a few Bc I’m indecisive)

“That’s gelfilte fish, skip that, and I’m gay.”

*sniffs* “Hi.”

“Guys, guys, guys, wanna something amazing?” *turns* “Hey, Jonah.”

“Wow! That’s so on brand for me!”

“Aaa I just suffer from hating things that hurt really bad-”

“You should see me when I’m really putting myself down. Actually you shouldn’t…it’s dark.”

“Probably because all my parents are shrinks. Passover’s fun.”

“Oh would you look at that? Saxophones.”

BROTP: Buffy and Cyrus, 100%. They are the ultimate best friends.

OTP: Jyrus, obviously. It’s my brand.

NOTP: Ciris. We don’t ship Cyrus with girls in this household :)

Random headcanon: Cyrus directing/writing the school play when he’s in high school.

Unpopular opinion: I don’t really know..is me thinking that Cyrus literally becomes the hulk when he’s mad an unpopular opinion? Lol.

Song I associate with them: Turning Out by AJR

Favorite picture of them:

..beautiful skskks

summary: 50 days of Andi Mack
body:
50 days of Andi Mack

Season 1 Episode 12: Best Surprise Ever

  • Cyrus embracing his inner playwright through Tater Theatre
  • “It’s just… I liked when we liked Jonah” Cyrus, dude, you need to start standing up for yourself
  • “All you have to say is Marty, I’m very, very…” “Confused?” Seriously, I love you Buffy but what?!
  • Marty’s mom is so cute!
  • The LOOKBACK!!!! I’m still getting feels from this ngl
  • “For lunch today I was thinking about going for baby carrots but now I’m thinking sliced kiwi!!” Looks like Bex’s rebellious nature is rubbing off on Cyrus
  • “Hey, lets get a practice early so you can do one of your frisbee tricks for me” 😊
  • Ok, but why are there pictures of Bex on the walls of random clubs?
  • It was a pretty big step for Buffy when she put her “friendship” with Marty ahead of her desire to win. She’s come so far in just 1 season and I’m so proud of her!
  • Cyrus casually lying on the ground is so me
  • Bowie’s song for Bex was beyond adorable but it would have been way more romantic if Andi wasn’t sitting right behind him…
  • I love how Andi finally got the message and left Bex and Bowie alone
  • “You’re in middle school, do you know how lucky you are to be dating me?“ I mean, she’s not wrong
  • Man, you just gotta love the good ol’ universe

summary: Tyrus Writing Prompt #1:
body:
Tyrus Writing Prompt #1:

An Unusual Arrangement

TJ, despite Cyrus’s best attempts to shut him up, is complaining about how there’s nowhere that he and Cy can go to have some “privacy.”

Parents won’t let them close doors. Parks, coffee shops, and movie theaters have other people. School is out of the question.

He’s been complaining for 20 minutes before Jonah finally looks up from his phone, and—like it’s nothing at all—offers, “Y’know, my parents never get home before 8. You guys can use my basement!”

summary: Why don't you like Reed so much?
question: Why don't you like Reed so much?
answer: He’s just a one-off character that the fandom hyped up too much. He was a plot device. He is irrelevant. He comes in handy for fics and stuff because there is no depth to his character, which gives more creative room to writers and creators. But in the context of the show, I just have absolutely no reason to care about him.

summary:
how bout we all start recognising that public figures and celebrities don't owe us anything. 
like, social media gives off the...
body:
how bout we all start recognising that public figures and celebrities don’t owe us anything.

like, social media gives off the illusion that people in the spotlight more accessible to fans than they are and that makes it easy to treat them like friends, but i feel like some fans out here need to learn that just because their idol interacts with some fans it doesn’t mean that they owe the rest of their fans personal interactions too. they don’t owe us anything.

public figures have their own lives, have every right to set boundaries without being harassed over it, and shouldn’t be treated like a commodity that every fan has the right to have access to. public figures are not obligated to interact with us. fan favouritism? not a thing. sometimes people make friends with their fans or talk to their fans but that doesn’t mean they should be pressured into talking to everyone else too.

let people live their lives without attacking them for not acknowledging everyone. that’s too much pressure for anyone, especially someone who is already under a spotlight, and it could end up in someone getting hurt.
